# Astro540 Homework 1

## Problem 1
* total proper motion $\mu$

$$
\mu = \sqrt{\mu_\delta^2 + \cos^2\delta\mu_\alpha^2}
$$

* proper motion velocity component

$$
v_\tau = \mu d = 0.376 \mathrm{pc} \cdot 1.21'' \mathrm{a^{-1}} = 2.16
\mathrm{km\cdot s^{-1}}
$$

* total velocity

$$
v  = \sqrt{v_tau^2 + v_r ^2} = \sqrt{7.6^2 + 2.16^2}\mathrm{km\cdot
s^{-1}}=7.9 \mathrm{km\cdot s^{-1}}
$$

* when teh object is closest to sun, the direction of its motion is
  perpendicular to the line connected it and the sun. Thus the
  distance is caculated as

$$
d_0 = d \cdot \sin\theta = 0.376 \mathrm{pc} \cdot \frac{v_\tau^2}{v} = 0.10 \mathrm{pc}
$$

* the proper motion

$$
\mu = \frac{v}{d_0}16.2''\mathrm{a^{-1}}
$$

